risc1.name: load
risc1.description: Loads a word from memory at location TOS (or num) and pushes it onto the register stack

risc1.name: loadf
risc1.description: Loads a word from the flag register and pushes it onto the register stack

risc1.name: store
risc1.description: Stores the word from TOS (or num) into memory to the location at TOS

risc1.name: storef
risc1.description: Stores the word from TOS into the flag register

risc1.name: swap
risc1.description: Swaps two top values from TOS (top of the register stack)

risc1.name: dup
risc1.description: Duplicates the top value from the register stack

risc1.name: dup2
risc1.description: Duplicates the second from top value from the register stack

risc1.name: mov
risc1.description: Pushes the value of num to the register stack

risc1.name: push
risc1.description: Pushes the word from TOS onto the memory stack

risc1.name: pushf
risc1.description: Pushes the word from the flag register onto the memory stack

risc1.name: pop
risc1.description: Pops the word from the memory stack onto top of the register stack

risc1.name: popf
risc1.description: Pops the word from the memory stack to the flag register

risc1.name: add
risc1.description: Adds two top values from TOS and pushes the result onto TOS

risc1.name: sub
risc1.description: Subtracts the second TOS from the top of the register stack, pushing the result onto it

risc1.name: mul
risc1.description: Multiplies two top values from TOS and pushes the result onto TOS

risc1.name: div
risc1.description: Divides the TOS value by the second from TOS, pushing the result onto it

risc1.name: and
risc1.description: Performs a binary and operation between two top TOS values, pushing the result onto it

risc1.name: or
risc1.description: Performs a bitwise or operation between two top TOS values, pushing the result onto it

risc1.name: xor
risc1.description: Performs a bitwise xor operation between two top TOS values, pushing the result onto it

risc1.name: not
risc1.description: Performs a bitwise not operation on TOS value, pushing the result onto the register stack

risc1.name: lsh
risc1.description: Performs a bitwise left shift operation on TOS value, moving it num bits to the left, and pushing the value onto TOS

risc1.name: rsh
risc1.description: Performs a bitwise right shift operation on TOS value, moving it num bits to the right, and pushing the value onto TOS

risc1.name: call
risc1.description: Pushes the next instruction's location on to the memory stack, transfers control by TOS or off instructions

risc1.name: ret
risc1.description: Returns control to the instruction saved on the memory stack

risc1.name: cmpe
risc1.description: Compares either two values on top of the register stack, or TOS and num for equality, pushing the result onto TOS (True is 0xffff, False is 0x0000)

risc1.name: cmpb
risc1.description: Compares either two values on top of the register stack, or TOS and num, determining whether the first is bigger than second. Pushing the result of the check onto TOS (True is 0xffff, False is 0x0000)

risc1.name: jmp
risc1.description: Unconditionally performs the jump by TOS (or off) instructions

risc1.name: jc
risc1.description: Checks whether the TOS value is True, and if it is, performs the jump by TOS (or off) instructions

risc1.name: in
risc1.description: Hangs the processor, waiting for the single-character user input on the device at the port specified, pushes it onto TOS

risc1.name: out
risc1.description: Transfers data from TOS to the device at port

risc1.name: nop
risc1.description: Does not do anything

risc2.name: load
risc2.description: Loads a word from memory at location IR into register ACC

risc2.name: loadf
risc2.description: Loads a word from the Flag Register into register ACC

risc2.name: loadi
risc2.description: Loads a word from the Index Register into register ACC

risc2.name: store
risc2.description: Stores a word from the ACC register or num to memory location at IR

risc2.name: storef
risc2.description: Stores a word from the ACC register into the Flag Register

risc2.name: storei
risc2.description: Stores a word from the ACC register into the Index Register

risc2.name: mov
risc2.description: Copies num into the ACC register

risc2.name: push
risc2.description: Pushes a word from the ACC register onto the memory stack

risc2.name: pushf
risc2.description: Pushes a word from the Flag Register onto the memory stack

risc2.name: pushi
risc2.description: Pushes a word from the Index Register onto the memory stack

risc2.name: pop
risc2.description: Pops a word from the memory stack into the ACC register

risc2.name: popf
risc2.description: Pops a word from the memory stack into the Flag Register

risc2.name: popi
risc2.description: Pops a word from the memory stack into the Index Register

risc2.name: add
risc2.description: Adds the values of the ACC register and memory at IR location, saving the result into ACC

risc2.name: inc
risc2.description: Increments the value in the ACC register by 1

risc2.name: dec
risc2.description: Decrements the value in the ACC register by 1

risc2.name: sub
risc2.description: Subtracts the value in memory at IR location from the value in ACC register, saving the result into ACC

risc2.name: mul
risc2.description: Multiplies the values of the ACC register and memory at IR location, saving the result into ACC

risc2.name: div
risc2.description: Divides the value at the ACC register by the value in memory at IR location, saving the result into ACC

risc2.name: and
risc2.description: Computes a bitwise and operation between ACC and memory location at IR and saves the result into ACC

risc2.name: or
risc2.description: Computes a bitwise or operation between ACC and memory location at IR and saves the result into ACC

risc2.name: xor
risc2.description: Computes a bitwise xor operation between ACC and memory location at IR and saves the result into ACC

risc2.name: not
risc2.description: Computes a bitwise not operation on the value of ACC

risc2.name: lsh
risc2.description: Shifts the ACC value to the left by $num bits

risc2.name: rsh
risc2.description: Shifts the ACC value to the right by $num bits

risc2.name: call
risc2.description: Pushes the next instruction's location on to the memory stack, transfers control by off (or ACC) instructions

risc2.name: ret
risc2.description: Returns control to the instruction saved on the memory stack

risc2.name: cmp
risc2.description: Subtracts the value in memory at IR location (or num) from ACC, changing the flags accordingly

risc2.name: test
risc2.description: Performs bitwise and operation between ACC and value in memory at IR location (or num), changing the flags accordingly

risc2.name: jmp
risc2.description: Jumps by off (or ACC) instructions unconditionally

risc2.name: je
risc2.description: Jumps by off (or ACC) instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was equal to the second

risc2.name: jne
risc2.description: Jumps by off (or ACC) instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was not equal to the second

risc2.name: jg
risc2.description: Jumps by off (or ACC) instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was greater than the second

risc2.name: jge
risc2.description: Jumps by off (or ACC) instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was greater or equal than the second

risc2.name: jl
risc2.description: Jumps by off (or ACC) instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was less than the second

risc2.name: jle
risc2.description: Jumps by off (or ACC) instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was less or equal than the second

risc2.name: in
risc2.description: Hangs the processor, waiting for the single-character user input on the device at the port specified, saving the result into ACC

risc2.name: out
risc2.description: Transfers data from ACC to the device at port

risc2.name: nop
risc2.description: Does not do anything

risc3.name: load
risc3.description: Loads a word from memory at location mem into register reg

risc3.name: store
risc3.description: Copies a word from the register reg and stores it in memory at location mem

risc3.name: mov_low
risc3.description: Copies the value of num into the lower (less significant) byte of reg

risc3.name: mov_high
risc3.description: Copies the value of num into the higher (more significant) byte of reg

risc3.name: mov
risc3.description: Copies the value of reg2 into reg1

risc3.name: push
risc3.description: Pushes the value of reg on the top of the memory stack

risc3.name: pop
risc3.description: Pops the value from the memory stack into reg

risc3.name: add
risc3.description: Adds the value of reg3 to the register reg2, saving the result in the register reg1

risc3.name: addc
risc3.description: Adds the value of the carry flag to the register reg2, saving the result in the register reg1

risc3.name: sub
risc3.description: Subtracts the value of reg3 from the register reg2, saving the result in the register reg1

risc3.name: mul
risc3.description: Multiplies the value from reg2 times reg3, saving the result in the register reg1

risc3.name: div
risc3.description: Divides the value from reg2 by reg3, saving the result in the register reg1

risc3.name: and
risc3.description: Computes a bitwise and operation between reg2 and reg3 and saves the result into reg1

risc3.name: or
risc3.description: Computes a bitwise or operation between reg2 and reg3 and saves the result into reg1

risc3.name: xor
risc3.description: Computes a bitwise xor operation between reg2 and reg3 and saves the result into reg1

risc3.name: not
risc3.description: Computes a bitwise not operation on reg2 and saves the result into reg1

risc3.name: lsh
risc3.description: Shifts the value from register reg2 by reg3 bits to the left, saving the result in the register reg1

risc3.name: rsh
risc3.description: Shifts the value from register reg2 by reg3 bits to the right, saving the result in the register reg1

risc3.name: call
risc3.description: Saves the next instruction's location to the Link Register, transfers control by off or reg instructions

risc3.name: ret
risc3.description: Transfers control back to the instruction saved in the Link Register

risc3.name: cmp
risc3.description: Subtracts the second value from the first one, changing the flags accordingly

risc3.name: test
risc3.description: Performs bitwise and operation between the reg1 and reg2, changing the flags accordingly

risc3.name: jmp
risc3.description: Jumps by off (or reg) instructions unconditionally

risc3.name: je
risc3.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was equal to the second

risc3.name: jne
risc3.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was not equal to the second

risc3.name: jg
risc3.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was greater than the second

risc3.name: jge
risc3.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was greater or equal than the second

risc3.name: jl
risc3.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was less than the second

risc3.name: jle
risc3.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was less or equal than the second

risc3.name: in
risc3.description: Hangs the processor, waiting for the single-character user input on the device at the port specified, saving the result into reg

risc3.name: out
risc3.description: Transfers data from num (or reg) to the device at port

risc3.name: nop
risc3.description: Does not do anything

cisc.name: mov
cisc.description: Copies a word from the right operand into the left (either into the register, or into memory at location pointed by the register, with offset specified by $off)

cisc.name: push
cisc.description: Pushes the value of reg or num on the top of the memory stack

cisc.name: pop
cisc.description: Pops the value from the memory stack into reg

cisc.name: enter
cisc.description: Replaces three instructions on moving the stack further own on new procedure call: push %bp / mov %bp, %sp / sub %sp, $num

cisc.name: leave
cisc.description: Replaces two instructions on return to the previous procedure's stack frame: mov %sp, %bp / pop %bp

cisc.name: add
cisc.description: Adds the value of the second operand to the first operand, saving the result in the first one

cisc.name: sub
cisc.description: Subtracts the value of the second operand from the first operand, saving the result in the first one

cisc.name: inc
cisc.description: Increments the value of the operand by one

cisc.name: dec
cisc.description: Decrements the value of the operand by one

cisc.name: mul
cisc.description: Multiplies two operands, saving the result in the first one

cisc.name: div
cisc.description: Divides the first operand by the second operand, saving the result in the first one

cisc.name: and
cisc.description: Computes a bitwise and operation between two operands and saves the result into the first one

cisc.name: or
cisc.description: Computes a bitwise or operation between two operands and saves the result into the first one

cisc.name: xor
cisc.description: Computes a bitwise xor operation between two operands and saves the result into the first one

cisc.name: not
cisc.description: Computes a bitwise not operation on the value of the operand

cisc.name: lsh
cisc.description: Shifts the value from the first operand by off bits to the left, saving the result in the first operand

cisc.name: rsh
cisc.description: Shifts the value from the first operand by off bits to the right, saving the result in the first operand

cisc.name: call
cisc.description: Saves the next instruction's location to the stack, transfers control by off, reg, or reg+off instructions

cisc.name: ret
cisc.description: Transfers control back to the instruction saved in the stack

cisc.name: cmp
cisc.description: Subtracts the second value from the first one, changing the flags accordingly

cisc.name: test
cisc.description: Performs bitwise and operation between the first operand and the second operand, changing the flags accordingly

cisc.name: jmp
cisc.description: Jumps by off, reg or reg+off instructions unconditionally

cisc.name: je
cisc.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was equal to the second

cisc.name: jne
cisc.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was not equal to the second

cisc.name: jg
cisc.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was greater than the second

cisc.name: jge
cisc.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was greater or equal than the second

cisc.name: jl
cisc.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was less than the second

cisc.name: jle
cisc.description: Jumps by off instructions if the first number in the compare instruction was less or equal than the second

cisc.name: in
cisc.description: Hangs the processor, waiting for the single-character user input on the device at the port specified, saving the result into reg

cisc.name: out
cisc.description: Transfers data from the second operand to the device at port

cisc.name: load4
cisc.description: SIMD operation: Loads four words starting from reg into four main registers: R00, R01, R02, R03

cisc.name: store4
cisc.description: SIMD operation: Stores main registers: R00, R01, R02, R03 into memory at location reg

cisc.name: add4
cisc.description: SIMD operation: Adds the value of reg to four values starting at reg location in memory

cisc.name: sub4
cisc.description: SIMD operation: Subtracts the value of reg from four values starting at reg location in memory

cisc.name: mul4
cisc.description: SIMD operation: Multiplies four values starting at reg location in memory by the value of reg

cisc.name: div4
cisc.description: SIMD operation: Divides four values starting at reg location in memory by the value of reg

cisc.name: nop
cisc.description: Does not do anything
